React component life-Cycle
* lifecycle refers to the different phases a component goes through from mounting to unmounting
* every react component has a lifecycle
* It goes through 3 main phases: Mounting, Updating, and Unmounting
* React provides lifecycle methods that allow developers to hook into these phases and perform specific actions at each stages

The Lifecycle of the component is division into three phases
1.Mounting (When component is added)
2.Unmounting (When component is removed)
3.Updating (When component updates)

Lifecycle Phases Overview:
--------------------------
mounting: First time on screen
1. Constructor() initialization
2. render()
3. componentDidMount() -(or useEffect [])
runs once when component is added to the DOM

Updating: When state/props
1. render()
2. componentDidUpdate() - (or useEffect [deps])
runs when component is updated due to state or props change

Unmounting: When component is removed
1. componentWillUnmount() - (or useEffect cleanup)
runs once when component is removed from the DOM

Life Cycle flow (class component)
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
|         MOUNTING          |        UPDATING (State / Props Change)           |                 UNMOUNTING                   |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| constructor()             | componentWillReceiveProps() (Deprecated)         | componentWillUnmount()                       |
| Initialize state          | Update state based on new props                  | Cleanup timers, listeners, subscriptions     |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
|            ↓              |                       ↓                          |                     ↓                        |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| render()                  | shouldComponentUpdate()                          | Component is removed from the DOM            |
| Return JSX                | Return true/false to decide re-render            |                                              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
|            ↓              |                       ↓                          |                                              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| componentDidMount()       | render()                                         |                                              |
| API calls                 | Re-render UI                                     |                                              |
| DOM interactions          |                                                  |                                              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
|            ↓              |                       ↓                          |                                              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
| Runs once when component  | componentDidUpdate()                             | Runs once when component is removed          |
| is added to the DOM       | API calls, DOM updates after changes             | from the DOM                                 |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+
|                           | Runs whenever state or props change              |                                              |
+---------------------------+--------------------------------------------------+----------------------------------------------+

class Example extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    this.state = { count: 0 };
    console.log('Constructor: Component is being initialized');
  }

  componentDidMount() {
    console.log('ComponentDidMount: Component has been mounted to the DOM');
  }

  componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState) {
    console.log('ComponentDidUpdate: Component has been updated');
  }

  componentWillUnmount() {
    console.log('ComponentWillUnmount: Component is about to be removed from the DOM');
  }

  render() {
    console.log('Render: Rendering the component');
  return <h3>Count: {this.state.count}</h3>;
  }
}
**Lifecycle Order:**
------------------
1. Constructor
2. Render
3. componentDidMount
4. Render (on state/props change)
5. componentDidUpdate
6. componentWillUnmount (when component is removed)

import {UseEffect} from 'react';
function Example({count}) {
  useEffect(() => {
    console.log('ComponentDidMount: Component has been mounted to the DOM');
    return () => {
      console.log('ComponentWillUnmount: Component is about to be removed from the DOM');
    };
  }, []);

  useEffect(() => {
    console.log('ComponentDidUpdate: Component has been updated');
  }, [count]);

  return <h3>Count: {count}</h3>;
}
**useEffect Guide:**
---------------
1. [] -> componentDidMount (runs once when component is mounted)
2. [deps] -> componentDidUpdate (runs when specified dependencies change)
3. return cleanup -> componentWillUnmount (runs when component is about to be removed from the DOM)

