**Higher Order Components (HOC)**
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Higher Order Components (HOCs) are functions that take a component as an argument and return a new component. These functions enhance the capabilities of the original component by adding additional props, behavior, or modifying its rendering logic.

Purpose:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
The primary purpose of HOCs is to promote code reuse and avoid duplication by extracting shared functionality from components into reusable functions. HOCs enable developers to encapsulate common patterns or behaviors and apply them to multiple components throughout the application.